    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.onStop() continuing a 4P match when multiple present avatars are tied at max score.",
      "The harness starts a real all-present 4P source round with max_score 2, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, forces avatars 4 and 3 to die first, then forces avatars 2 and 1 to die together in the next source update.",
      "Because Game.update() captures deaths.count() at frame start, avatars 2 and 1 both resolve to score 2; source isWon() sees tied leaders at max score and starts the next round instead of emitting end.",
      "This is a JS-oracle source fixture only. It does not claim Python source-runner parity, vector lifecycle parity, public-env parity, replay, trainer observations, bonuses, wire behavior, or pixels."
    ]
  },
